section.section:
This subsection applies to:
a society;
a person acting for the society;
an insurance producer that acts on behalf of a fraternal benefit society; and
a person acting for an insurance producer that acts on behalf of a fraternal benefit society.

text.section:
A society member may not receive or accept, directly or indirectly:
a rebate of all or part of a premium payable on a certificate;
a rebate of a fraternal benefit agent's commission on a premium payable on a certificate;
any favor, advantage, or share in the dividends or other benefits to accrue on the insurance contract; or
any other valuable consideration or inducement not specified in the insurance contract.
